Subject: [PATCH 1/7] feat: add IndexQueryPlanner for index reconciliation
 query plan
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adaptive lexical-prefix strategy that tiles the search index into fetch
buckets each ≤ 100K chunks. Uses $top=0 count-only queries — no document
enumeration, no $skip wall. Recursively subdivides hex-prefix buckets
until every leaf is within target. Single regime handles both random and
sequential GUIDs without special-casing.

- IndexQueryPlanner: core planner with recursive SubdivideAsync
- IndexQueryPlan / QueryPlanEntry: result types
- IndexQueryPlannerOptions: Target (default 80K) + OutputPath
- IndexQueryPlannerTests: integration test writing plan to temp file

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
